{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584957","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584957"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:01:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:01:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14841"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14841","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14841"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.84,0.14,0,0.02,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7532"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114902"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7532","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7532"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14841"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96908"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"7881"},{"type":"tags","id":"9830"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18434"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18545"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114902"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EConsider the major components that make up human blood.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following makes up the highest proportion by volume in human blood?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Plasma","Erythrocytes","Leukocytes","Platelets","Proteins"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EBlood consists of two main components: \u003Cstrong\u003Eplasma\u003C/strong\u003E and formed elements. \u003Cstrong\u003EPlasma\u003C/strong\u003E makes up approximately 55% of total blood volume and is the liquid portion containing water, proteins, electrolytes, nutrients, and waste products.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe formed elements include \u003Cstrong\u003Eerythrocytes\u003C/strong\u003E (red blood cells) which comprise about 45% of total blood volume, whilst \u003Cstrong\u003Eleukocytes\u003C/strong\u003E (white blood cells) and \u003Cstrong\u003Eplatelets\u003C/strong\u003E each make up less than 1% of blood volume. \u003Cstrong\u003EProteins\u003C/strong\u003E are dissolved within plasma and make up approximately 7-8% of plasma volume.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Blood is composed of approximately 55% plasma and 45% formed elements, with erythrocytes making up the vast majority of cellular components.","The cellular composition of blood includes approximately 4-6 million erythrocytes/\u00b5L compared to 4,000-11,000 leukocytes/\u00b5L and 150,000-450,000 platelets/\u00b5L."],"references":["Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., Fausto, N., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (2014). Robbins and Cotran pathologic basis of disease, professional edition e-book. Elsevier health sciences","Dean L. Blood Groups and Red Cell Antigens [Internet]. Bethesda (MD): National Center for Biotechnology Information (US); 2005. Chapter 1, Blood and the cells it contains. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK2263/","Mathew J, Sankar P, Varacallo M. Physiology, Blood Plasma. [Updated 2023 Apr 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK531504/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96908"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14841"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96908","links":{"self"